1
00:01:37,916 --> 00:01:41,000
[DERRIDA] Please miss! I've
been lost in the snow for hours!

2
00:01:41,083 --> 00:01:43,291
Do you know where
a sweet girl named Mage lives?

3
00:01:43,375 --> 00:01:44,958
You made it! Come in!

4
00:01:45,041 --> 00:01:47,166
[BOTH laughing]

5
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:50,291
♪

6
00:01:57,541 --> 00:01:59,708
[DERRIDA] My memories have
definitely been changed.

7
00:02:01,625 --> 00:02:03,875
You mean her birthday
party 10 years ago?

8
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,541
But, you were late that day.

9
00:02:06,625 --> 00:02:08,041
Huh?

10
00:02:08,125 --> 00:02:10,250
[YURI] I mean, you got there
after I did, at least.

11
00:02:10,333 --> 00:02:11,125
[click]

12
00:02:11,208 --> 00:02:12,166
Hmm...

13
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:13,666
[MAGE]
Coming!

14
00:02:14,625 --> 00:02:15,458
[doors creak]

15
00:02:15,541 --> 00:02:17,208
You're late, Derrida!

16
00:02:17,291 --> 00:02:18,416
-[thud]
-[grunt]

17
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:19,916
[YURI laughing]

18
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,041
[DERRIDA]
Uh, happy birthday, Mage!

19
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:26,750
[DERRIDA]
Did I... change things...

20
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:29,166
with a time ride?

21
00:02:29,250 --> 00:02:31,291
Did I experience
a different past?

22
00:02:33,541 --> 00:02:35,666
[DERRIDA]
Uh, happy birthday, Mage!

23
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:36,958
[laughing]

24
00:02:37,041 --> 00:02:38,916
It's not that funny,
stop laughing!

25
00:02:41,041 --> 00:02:44,500
Does that mean the time ride
was a success after all?

26
00:02:44,583 --> 00:02:46,166
[grunt]

27
00:02:46,250 --> 00:02:48,125
-[YURI] Derrida!
-Hmm?

28
00:02:48,208 --> 00:02:49,250
We've got one!

29
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:51,583
It's a clue about Mage!

30
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:53,708
[typing]

31
00:02:55,166 --> 00:02:56,541
[YURI]
Here, take a look.

32
00:02:56,625 --> 00:02:59,833
Vanfort Museum of Modern Life?

33
00:02:59,916 --> 00:03:02,041
-What'd she be doing there?
-[YURI sighs]

34
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:04,916
[YURI] I don't know,
but maybe we can find a hint?

35
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,083
That museum's not
that far from here.

36
00:03:08,166 --> 00:03:09,541
[engine roaring]

37
00:03:09,625 --> 00:03:11,083
[MAYUKA]
It's supposed to be a really,

38
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:14,208
really big museum right?
What kind of stuff do they have?

39
00:03:14,291 --> 00:03:17,208
[YURI] Um...
I've actually never been there.

40
00:03:17,291 --> 00:03:19,500
Derrida, I need to take care

41
00:03:19,583 --> 00:03:21,416
of some business of my
own while we're there.

42
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:22,666
Sure, like what?

43
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:25,291
There's a request
that I was given.

44
00:03:25,375 --> 00:03:27,333
Just something
I was asked to retrieve,

45
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:29,333
if I was ever in Vanfort.

46
00:03:29,416 --> 00:03:31,375
It shouldn't really
take too much time.

47
00:03:31,458 --> 00:03:32,708
Understood.

48
00:03:32,791 --> 00:03:34,333
You do whatever
you gotta do then.

49
00:03:34,416 --> 00:03:36,791
[engine roaring, dust flying]

50
00:03:36,875 --> 00:03:38,583
[chuckle]

51
00:03:39,791 --> 00:03:41,458
Found you.

52
00:03:41,541 --> 00:03:44,583
♪

53
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:49,500
[buzzing]

54
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:52,500
[DERRIDA]
It's totally deserted.

55
00:03:55,708 --> 00:03:58,791
[YURI] There was a major battle
here about a year ago, I think.

56
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,000
[gasp]

57
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:06,666
Do I hafta stay here again?

58
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:08,916
We don't know what
we might run into.

59
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,625
[YURI] You can't always
just leave her here.

60
00:04:11,708 --> 00:04:13,791
I don't bring her
with me on jobs.

61
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:14,833
[YURI]
Okay.

62
00:04:15,791 --> 00:04:17,666
I'll show you some
pictures later, Mayuka.

63
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:19,458
Yay! You're the best, Big Sis!

64
00:04:19,541 --> 00:04:21,833
And you're not, Papa.
[pout]

65
00:04:21,916 --> 00:04:23,208
-[VIDAUX grumbles]
-She just misses you.

66
00:04:23,291 --> 00:04:24,583
Let's go so we can hurry back.

67
00:04:24,666 --> 00:04:26,375
[VIDAUX]
Fine.

68
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:32,791
[doors creak]

69
00:04:36,041 --> 00:04:38,166
What was this building used
for back in the day anyway?

70
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:40,625
♪

71
00:04:40,708 --> 00:04:43,000
[DERRIDA]
It was a police station.

72
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:44,500
-[debris crumbling]
-[YURI, DERRIDA gasp]

73
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:49,250
-[DERRIDA] An Automata?
-[humming]

74
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:51,208
[AUTOMATA]
Intruders detected.

75
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:52,791
-[click]
-Do not attempt to resist.

76
00:04:52,875 --> 00:04:54,208
Put your hands up.

77
00:04:54,291 --> 00:04:56,416
-[DERRIDA] Is it broken?
-[VIDAUX] What's wrong?

78
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:59,083
Hmm...
There's no way.

79
00:04:59,166 --> 00:05:01,583
[AUTOMATA]
Initiating facial recognition.

80
00:05:01,666 --> 00:05:03,208
Confirmed. Inspector Volker.

81
00:05:03,291 --> 00:05:04,708
-[buzzing]
-[clicking]

82
00:05:04,791 --> 00:05:06,541
Switching to support mode.

83
00:05:06,625 --> 00:05:09,500
[winding down]

84
00:05:09,583 --> 00:05:11,666
-Uh...
-[gasp]

85
00:05:12,708 --> 00:05:14,125
[YURI]
It shut down.

86
00:05:15,250 --> 00:05:16,333
Inspector, huh?

87
00:05:17,291 --> 00:05:19,083
Not for a long time now.

88
00:05:20,083 --> 00:05:22,625
[VIDAUX] So, some of them
are still operational.

89
00:05:22,708 --> 00:05:24,750
[YURI] Didn't take
you for a policeman.

90
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:40,041
There you are.

91
00:05:43,666 --> 00:05:45,250
[DERRIDA] This is one of
the later-generation

92
00:05:45,333 --> 00:05:47,291
police models
put out by Rebuild.

93
00:05:47,375 --> 00:05:49,625
They were pretty
compact by then.

94
00:05:49,708 --> 00:05:52,000
Were you the one
that developed them?

95
00:05:52,083 --> 00:05:54,416
Only the base system.

96
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:56,208
I wasn't directly involved.

97
00:05:56,291 --> 00:05:57,541
-[YURI sighs]
-[footsteps]

98
00:05:57,625 --> 00:05:59,000
[VIDAUX]
Okay, I'm back.

99
00:05:59,083 --> 00:06:00,958
Let's head for the museum.

100
00:06:01,041 --> 00:06:02,166
[wind blowing]

101
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:05,958
-[YURI giggling]
-[snapping pictures]

102
00:06:06,041 --> 00:06:08,333
I can't wait for
Mayuka to see these!

103
00:06:08,416 --> 00:06:10,666
[DERRIDA]
Strange. I feel like...

104
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:12,291
I've been here before.

105
00:06:12,375 --> 00:06:14,208
Huh?

106
00:06:16,666 --> 00:06:18,708
[breeze blowing]

107
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:22,708
Wow! It's huge!

108
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:26,875
♪

109
00:06:26,958 --> 00:06:29,000
[wind howling]

110
00:06:31,083 --> 00:06:33,708
[gasping]

111
00:06:33,791 --> 00:06:36,541
[clock ticking slowly]

112
00:06:36,625 --> 00:06:38,666
♪

113
00:06:41,125 --> 00:06:42,375
[gasp]

114
00:06:44,375 --> 00:06:45,458
[laughing]

115
00:06:45,541 --> 00:06:47,583
[rumbling]

116
00:06:50,083 --> 00:06:51,125
[doors slide]

117
00:06:55,041 --> 00:06:55,916
[laugh]

118
00:06:59,958 --> 00:07:00,833
[clock ticking slowly]

119
00:07:00,916 --> 00:07:02,625
I'm with Dad?

120
00:07:02,708 --> 00:07:05,208
Did... I ever go out
with him like this?

121
00:07:05,291 --> 00:07:06,291
[wind blowing]

122
00:07:06,375 --> 00:07:07,250
[groan]

123
00:07:08,208 --> 00:07:09,625
What's going on here?

124
00:07:09,708 --> 00:07:11,750
[footsteps]

125
00:07:27,416 --> 00:07:29,916
[YURI]
Look at that. A celestial globe?

126
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,500
[gasp]

127
00:07:31,583 --> 00:07:32,916
[YURI]
I know this!

128
00:07:33,875 --> 00:07:36,375
[beeping, humming]

129
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:38,666
[pulse]

130
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:40,708
[sparkling]

131
00:07:40,791 --> 00:07:44,541
♪

132
00:07:44,625 --> 00:07:48,041
Oh, wow! It's gorgeous!
How pretty!

133
00:07:56,166 --> 00:07:57,625
[YOUNG DERRIDA]
So cool!

134
00:07:57,708 --> 00:07:59,000
[gasp]

135
00:08:02,291 --> 00:08:04,041
[YOUNG DERRIDA]
Don't you think so, Dad?

136
00:08:05,250 --> 00:08:06,875
[JACQUES]
Try looking at it from the side.

137
00:08:06,958 --> 00:08:08,416
Huh?

138
00:08:14,041 --> 00:08:15,208
[YOUNG DERRIDA gasps, laughs]

139
00:08:15,291 --> 00:08:16,875
It looks totally different!

140
00:08:16,958 --> 00:08:18,791
From the side, you can see
which ones are closer

141
00:08:18,875 --> 00:08:20,333
and which are further away!

142
00:08:21,291 --> 00:08:22,583
Dad, listen!

143
00:08:22,666 --> 00:08:24,541
The starlight in the sky
is from a long time ago,

144
00:08:24,625 --> 00:08:26,416
but we're just
seeing it now, right?

145
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:30,166
Yes. If a star's farther away,

146
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:31,958
the light takes
longer to reach us.

147
00:08:32,041 --> 00:08:33,875
That's the science.

148
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:35,416
♪

149
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,875
[DERRIDA] Starlight makes
a long journey across space.

150
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:39,666
In some cases,
it reaches our eyes

151
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:42,291
only after hundreds
or even millions of years.

152
00:08:42,375 --> 00:08:44,375
Amazing, huh?

153
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:46,875
It's like, even though we may
exist in different millennia,

154
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:49,333
we're still somehow connected
in this moment together,

155
00:08:49,416 --> 00:08:51,333
meeting across time and space.

156
00:08:52,291 --> 00:08:56,250
"Starlight is essentially
a natural time machine." Huh.

157
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:57,875
[YURI]
Huh? What's that?

158
00:08:58,833 --> 00:09:00,833
[DERRIDA]
Something my father said.

159
00:09:00,916 --> 00:09:02,958
[wind whistling]

160
00:09:06,333 --> 00:09:08,333
[YURI] Why do you
think Mage came here?

161
00:09:09,291 --> 00:09:11,166
[VIDAUX] If we get our hands
on some security footage,

162
00:09:11,250 --> 00:09:12,458
we might find out.

163
00:09:12,541 --> 00:09:14,833
But how would we manage that?

164
00:09:17,208 --> 00:09:18,000
[DERRIDA gasps]

165
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:19,916
♪

166
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,666
[crackling, wind blowing]

167
00:09:22,791 --> 00:09:24,708
What in the...

168
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:31,083
Derrida, where are you going?

169
00:09:31,166 --> 00:09:34,166
[wind howling]

170
00:09:34,250 --> 00:09:35,041
[grimace]

171
00:09:35,125 --> 00:09:37,166
[clock ticking slowly]

172
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:41,416
[laughing]

173
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:45,875
[continues laughing]

174
00:09:47,916 --> 00:09:50,666
That memory... but why now?

175
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:53,708
[VIDAUX]
Hey, don't go off alone!

176
00:09:53,791 --> 00:09:55,500
Come back here!

177
00:09:55,583 --> 00:09:56,958
[groan]
Remember...

178
00:09:57,041 --> 00:09:59,333
[crash, rumbling]

179
00:10:00,916 --> 00:10:01,916
[gasp]

180
00:10:02,875 --> 00:10:03,750
[VIDAUX]
Derrida!

181
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:05,000
Not you again.

182
00:10:05,083 --> 00:10:06,500
-[grunt]
-[slice]

183
00:10:06,583 --> 00:10:08,791
-Get outta here now!
-[BOTH gasp]

184
00:10:10,083 --> 00:10:10,958
[grunt]

185
00:10:12,375 --> 00:10:13,208
[gasp]

186
00:10:13,291 --> 00:10:14,166
[grunt]

187
00:10:15,291 --> 00:10:16,333
[blast]

188
00:10:16,416 --> 00:10:17,625
You're in the way.

189
00:10:17,708 --> 00:10:19,333
I'm just doing my job.

190
00:10:20,291 --> 00:10:22,416
[panting]
Yuri! Are you hurt?

191
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:23,791
No.

192
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:26,708
You tell your employer this.

193
00:10:26,791 --> 00:10:29,416
No one gets to Derrida,
except through me.

194
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,041
♪

195
00:10:31,125 --> 00:10:32,000
[chuckle]

196
00:10:32,958 --> 00:10:34,750
[footsteps]

197
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:36,541
[panting]

198
00:10:38,666 --> 00:10:40,541
-Huh?
-What's wrong?

199
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:42,708
[YURI]
My camera...

200
00:10:42,791 --> 00:10:45,166
[gasp]
From when you fell earlier?

201
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:46,500
[sniffle]

202
00:10:46,583 --> 00:10:48,166
You okay?

203
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:50,708
Yeah. Let's go
and find that footage.

204
00:10:52,875 --> 00:10:54,625
Oh, Yuri.

205
00:10:54,708 --> 00:10:55,708
[wind howling]

206
00:10:55,791 --> 00:10:58,125
[clock ticking slowly]

207
00:11:00,666 --> 00:11:02,125
[JACQUES]
Derrida!

208
00:11:02,208 --> 00:11:03,583
[YOUNG DERRIDA]
Dad!

209
00:11:04,541 --> 00:11:07,333
I'm sorry. I...

210
00:11:07,416 --> 00:11:09,041
I won't run off again,
I promise.

211
00:11:10,666 --> 00:11:12,041
[DERRIDA]
That's right...

212
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,875
When we came here back then,

213
00:11:14,958 --> 00:11:16,416
I got lost, and...

214
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:17,416
-[footsteps]
-[YURI] Huh?

215
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:19,916
Hey, where are you going?

216
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,708
[doors opening, hissing]

217
00:11:22,666 --> 00:11:24,916
[YURI]
Is this the security room?

218
00:11:26,083 --> 00:11:27,791
[DERRIDA] We need the monitor
with a memory card.

219
00:11:27,875 --> 00:11:29,541
[YURI]
I'll take a look.

220
00:11:29,625 --> 00:11:32,083
-[beeping]
-If I can just narrow it down

221
00:11:32,166 --> 00:11:33,916
to only locations
where Mage was, then...

222
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,666
[beeping, hissing]

223
00:11:36,750 --> 00:11:38,041
There!

224
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,458
I've copied the footage of Mage.

225
00:11:40,541 --> 00:11:42,625
It's here on this chip.

226
00:11:43,583 --> 00:11:44,583
Great.

227
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:48,333
I can't believe you just
guessed where it was!

228
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:51,375
I've actually been here before,
I'd just forgotten!

229
00:11:51,458 --> 00:11:52,416
Huh?

230
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:54,291
Anyway, let's go!

231
00:11:54,375 --> 00:11:55,375
[gasp]

232
00:11:55,458 --> 00:11:57,208
[YURI]
What now?

233
00:11:57,291 --> 00:11:58,666
-[DERRIDA groaning]
-Are you hurt?

234
00:11:58,750 --> 00:12:00,958
[DERRIDA]
It's no use. I can't go yet.

235
00:12:01,041 --> 00:12:02,041
[YURI]
Uh...

236
00:12:02,125 --> 00:12:03,708
-[air rushing]
-[panting]

237
00:12:03,791 --> 00:12:05,708
♪

238
00:12:05,791 --> 00:12:07,750
[DERRIDA] There's another
important memory here.

239
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:08,625
[grunt]

240
00:12:08,708 --> 00:12:09,833
[YURI]
Huh?

241
00:12:09,916 --> 00:12:11,583
[panting]

242
00:12:11,666 --> 00:12:13,916
Hey, Derrida, hold on! Wait up!

243
00:12:14,875 --> 00:12:16,833
[panting]

244
00:12:16,916 --> 00:12:19,875
[footsteps]

245
00:12:23,916 --> 00:12:25,375
[gasp]

246
00:12:25,458 --> 00:12:26,916
No way...

247
00:12:27,875 --> 00:12:30,125
This is the prototype,
the first Automata.

248
00:12:31,416 --> 00:12:34,083
Yes, of course.
That was the day...

249
00:12:40,708 --> 00:12:42,333
My father and I were here.

250
00:12:42,416 --> 00:12:44,291
We came for its
public unveiling.

251
00:12:50,958 --> 00:12:53,541
[electric motors whirring]

252
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:58,458
Whoa...
[gasp]

253
00:12:59,416 --> 00:13:00,458
[laugh]

254
00:13:00,541 --> 00:13:01,333
[DERRIDA]
That's right.

255
00:13:01,416 --> 00:13:03,000
When I was little,

256
00:13:03,083 --> 00:13:05,875
Dad was nothing short
of a hero in my eyes.

257
00:13:05,958 --> 00:13:07,250
♪

258
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:09,333
Such an important memory.

259
00:13:09,416 --> 00:13:11,916
How could I have
forgotten it for so long?

260
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,375
[YURI]
"2039.

261
00:13:14,458 --> 00:13:17,708
Automata prototype
commemoration ceremony."

262
00:13:18,708 --> 00:13:20,916
Inventor, Jacques Yvain.

263
00:13:25,583 --> 00:13:27,041
Sorry, Dad.

264
00:13:27,125 --> 00:13:28,791
[grunting]

265
00:13:28,875 --> 00:13:30,875
[crying]

266
00:13:30,958 --> 00:13:32,916
If only I'd
remembered this before.

267
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,791
I was always fighting with him.

268
00:13:34,875 --> 00:13:36,791
And I was too late
to warn him, too.

269
00:13:36,875 --> 00:13:38,041
I...

270
00:13:38,125 --> 00:13:40,250
-[crackling]
-[humming]

271
00:13:40,333 --> 00:13:42,708
[clock ticking slowly]

272
00:13:42,791 --> 00:13:43,666
[gasp]

273
00:13:45,166 --> 00:13:47,000
[ANGE] Feelings at odds
with each other.

274
00:13:47,083 --> 00:13:49,625
Two people's timelines
that never overlapped.

275
00:13:50,583 --> 00:13:52,791
If you could spin
those threads anew...

276
00:13:52,875 --> 00:13:54,583
[ticking]

277
00:13:57,416 --> 00:13:59,541
[energy surging, bang]

278
00:13:59,625 --> 00:14:00,583
[gasp]

279
00:14:00,666 --> 00:14:03,500
[air rushing]

280
00:14:04,458 --> 00:14:06,916
Ah!
[grunting]

281
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,291
[screaming]

282
00:14:09,375 --> 00:14:10,166
[mechanical clicking]

283
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:11,291
[gasp]

284
00:14:13,166 --> 00:14:15,791
♪

285
00:14:15,875 --> 00:14:17,166
[DERRIDA]
Where am I?

286
00:14:18,250 --> 00:14:19,083
Hmm?

287
00:14:21,625 --> 00:14:22,916
What the...

288
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,083
Can it really be the day
after Mage's birthday?

289
00:14:25,166 --> 00:14:26,583
Could I have time jumped?

290
00:14:27,666 --> 00:14:28,958
[sigh]

291
00:14:29,041 --> 00:14:30,625
Any reply from Jacques Yvain?

292
00:14:30,708 --> 00:14:32,541
[COMPUTER A] Your appointment
today was confirmed.

293
00:14:32,625 --> 00:14:33,791
Meeting site designated.

294
00:14:33,875 --> 00:14:35,416
[sigh]

295
00:14:38,083 --> 00:14:39,666
Dad...

296
00:14:40,958 --> 00:14:43,541
[WOMAN, overlapping]
Clockwise. Anti-clockwise.

297
00:14:46,541 --> 00:14:47,791
[music playing]

298
00:14:47,875 --> 00:14:49,833
[ANNOUNCER]
Welcome to a reinvented world.

299
00:14:49,916 --> 00:14:51,250
[rumbling]

300
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:55,833
[tires screech]

301
00:14:55,916 --> 00:14:57,208
-[door hisses]
-[car winds down]

302
00:14:57,291 --> 00:14:58,666
I don't have time to
wait for the meeting.

303
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:00,958
I need to talk to him right now!

304
00:15:01,916 --> 00:15:03,666
Hey, Dad!
You're in there, right?

305
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:04,875
Open up! It's me, Derrida!

306
00:15:04,958 --> 00:15:07,000
[COMPUTER B]
Retinal scan complete.

307
00:15:07,083 --> 00:15:08,375
-Confirmed. Derrida Yvain.
-[banging]

308
00:15:08,458 --> 00:15:09,916
-[doors slide]
-[panting]

309
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,291
Dad!

310
00:15:12,958 --> 00:15:14,416
He's not here yet.

311
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,416
I need to find him
and tell him about Andrei

312
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:17,625
as soon as possible.

313
00:15:17,708 --> 00:15:19,083
[COMPUTER C]
How can I help you?

314
00:15:19,166 --> 00:15:21,291
[DERRIDA] What's Jaques Yvain's
current location?

315
00:15:21,375 --> 00:15:22,875
[COMPUTER C]
Location unknown.

316
00:15:22,958 --> 00:15:25,125
GPS is not
currently functioning.

317
00:15:25,208 --> 00:15:28,625
Calendar contains an appointment
with his son this evening.

318
00:15:28,708 --> 00:15:29,583
[DERRIDA]
Huh?

319
00:15:32,125 --> 00:15:33,458
Dad...

320
00:15:33,541 --> 00:15:35,541
♪

321
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:41,291
[footsteps]

322
00:15:41,375 --> 00:15:42,416
[gasp]

323
00:15:49,666 --> 00:15:51,291
[JACQUES]
You're here already?

324
00:15:51,375 --> 00:15:52,666
Huh?

325
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:54,541
It's been a while.

326
00:15:54,625 --> 00:15:57,000
How's work been treating
you lately, then?

327
00:15:57,083 --> 00:15:59,083
[DERRIDA] We don't have
any time for small talk.

328
00:15:59,166 --> 00:16:01,916
Listen, you have
to run away with me!

329
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,750
[gasp]

330
00:16:05,791 --> 00:16:07,500
[JACQUES] Andrei's
going to try to kill me?

331
00:16:07,583 --> 00:16:09,083
Yes.

332
00:16:09,166 --> 00:16:11,708
He already knows all
about the DZ bug.

333
00:16:11,791 --> 00:16:13,500
He's going to try
to eliminate us

334
00:16:13,583 --> 00:16:15,916
before we can do
something about it.

335
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:16,958
I see.

336
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:18,541
I thought as much.

337
00:16:18,625 --> 00:16:19,500
[DERRIDA]
Huh?

338
00:16:23,833 --> 00:16:25,500
[JACQUES]
Derrida,

339
00:16:25,583 --> 00:16:27,791
you need to get yourself out of
this mess as soon as possible.

340
00:16:27,875 --> 00:16:29,083
Wait, are you telling me

341
00:16:29,166 --> 00:16:31,000
that you already knew
what was going on?

342
00:16:31,083 --> 00:16:32,875
[JACQUES]
Yes, and I also knew that

343
00:16:32,958 --> 00:16:35,833
fixing the bug with a patch
wouldn't make a difference now.

344
00:16:35,916 --> 00:16:37,250
Then you know as well as I do

345
00:16:37,333 --> 00:16:39,083
that we need to get away
from here right now!

346
00:16:39,166 --> 00:16:41,000
[JACQUES]
Absolutely not!

347
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:42,833
I have a responsibility.

348
00:16:42,916 --> 00:16:45,750
I couldn't do anything
about the buggy DZs,

349
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:48,541
so I have to see
this through to the end.

350
00:16:48,625 --> 00:16:50,416
No, you can't!

351
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:51,250
That's crazy talk!

352
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:53,000
Listen, son.

353
00:16:53,083 --> 00:16:54,333
I wasn't able to make a patch,

354
00:16:54,416 --> 00:16:56,375
but I had a feeling
that you could.

355
00:16:56,458 --> 00:16:58,250
I was right about that,
wasn't I?

356
00:16:59,208 --> 00:17:00,291
[DERRIDA]
Wha?

357
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:02,541
I knew, it was only
a matter of time

358
00:17:02,625 --> 00:17:04,375
before you surpassed me.

359
00:17:04,458 --> 00:17:05,500
I'm proud of you.

360
00:17:05,583 --> 00:17:07,125
[DERRIDA]
Wha... Y--

361
00:17:07,208 --> 00:17:08,333
You're saying that now?

362
00:17:09,250 --> 00:17:11,875
[JACQUES] That's why the world
can't afford to lose you,

363
00:17:11,958 --> 00:17:13,583
and neither can I.

364
00:17:13,666 --> 00:17:15,666
I don't want to lose my son.

365
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:17,458
Leave this to me,
and get out of here!

366
00:17:17,541 --> 00:17:19,916
I'll go, but, Dad,
you need to come with me, too!

367
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,333
Those words mean a lot to me.

368
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:23,583
Thank you.

369
00:17:23,666 --> 00:17:25,083
But you have to go alone.

370
00:17:25,166 --> 00:17:27,500
You must run away and live.

371
00:17:27,583 --> 00:17:28,958
[DERRIDA]
I can't go without you!

372
00:17:29,041 --> 00:17:30,875
I won't let you die for
nothing because of them!

373
00:17:30,958 --> 00:17:32,166
[echoing gasp]

374
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:35,833
Wait! Dad, no!
[panting]

375
00:17:36,791 --> 00:17:38,541
Dad!

376
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:40,291
♪

377
00:17:40,375 --> 00:17:42,291
[clock ticking slowly]

378
00:17:42,375 --> 00:17:44,250
[heavy breathing]

379
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:46,875
[ticking]

380
00:17:49,250 --> 00:17:52,291
-[energy surging]
-[mechanical clicking]

381
00:17:59,875 --> 00:18:00,750
[bang]

382
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:05,750
I couldn't stop it.

383
00:18:05,833 --> 00:18:07,083
Uh...

384
00:18:08,083 --> 00:18:10,208
Maybe, if I could
just go back...

385
00:18:11,166 --> 00:18:14,458
Remember the past,
all your memories.

386
00:18:14,541 --> 00:18:17,333
If I can just make it
back to Dad!

387
00:18:17,416 --> 00:18:18,208
[sigh]

388
00:18:18,291 --> 00:18:19,166
Derrida?

389
00:18:20,416 --> 00:18:22,791
[heavy breathing, groaning]

390
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:25,583
Just let me go back
one more time!

391
00:18:25,666 --> 00:18:28,750
I have to get back there!
I finally remembered!

392
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:30,875
I was going to fix it!

393
00:18:30,958 --> 00:18:32,083
Dad!
[grunt]

394
00:18:32,166 --> 00:18:34,666
[crying]

395
00:18:34,750 --> 00:18:36,125
-[crash]
-[gasp]

396
00:18:36,208 --> 00:18:38,791
-We have to leave, now!
-[crying]

397
00:18:38,875 --> 00:18:40,208
Come on!

398
00:18:40,291 --> 00:18:42,708
-Pull yourself together! [grunt]
-[groan]

399
00:18:42,791 --> 00:18:44,583
I don't know what's
going on with you,

400
00:18:44,666 --> 00:18:47,500
but stop being such a crybaby
and save your tears for later!

401
00:18:47,583 --> 00:18:49,083
We can't afford to die here!

402
00:18:49,166 --> 00:18:50,041
[grunt]

403
00:18:50,125 --> 00:18:51,833
I-I'm sorry.

404
00:18:51,916 --> 00:18:53,375
Huh? Your camera.

405
00:18:54,833 --> 00:18:56,500
Wasn't it broken before?

406
00:18:56,583 --> 00:18:57,791
[YURI]
What are you talking about?

407
00:18:57,875 --> 00:18:58,916
[gasp]

408
00:19:00,458 --> 00:19:02,333
♪

409
00:19:03,833 --> 00:19:05,666
[rumbling, crash]

410
00:19:07,541 --> 00:19:09,833
[debris falling]

411
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:10,791
[grunt]

412
00:19:11,958 --> 00:19:12,916
[VIDAUX]
Move!

413
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:13,916
[grunt]

414
00:19:15,958 --> 00:19:17,291
-[grunt]
-[explosion]

415
00:19:19,041 --> 00:19:20,125
-[gasp]
-[screaming]

416
00:19:20,208 --> 00:19:21,166
[crash]

417
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:22,125
Huh?

418
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:25,000
[gasp]

419
00:19:25,958 --> 00:19:28,000
[DERRIDA]
You... protected us?

420
00:19:29,250 --> 00:19:30,291
[smash]

421
00:19:32,208 --> 00:19:34,000
-[grunt]
-[bang, clatter]

422
00:19:34,083 --> 00:19:35,750
[VIDAUX]
Don't worry about it!

423
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:38,416
It was only doing what
it's programmed for!

424
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:40,875
[grunt]

425
00:19:40,958 --> 00:19:42,916
[blasting, metal shattering]

426
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:43,916
[gasp]

427
00:19:45,166 --> 00:19:46,750
[glass shattering]

428
00:19:48,125 --> 00:19:49,375
[panting]

429
00:19:53,666 --> 00:19:54,708
[explosion]

430
00:19:56,083 --> 00:19:58,333
[rumbling]

431
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,541
[sigh]

432
00:20:04,625 --> 00:20:05,666
[smash]

433
00:20:06,625 --> 00:20:08,666
[breeze blowing]

434
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,708
Hey, you guys! We're over here!

435
00:20:13,791 --> 00:20:15,208
It's Mayuka!

436
00:20:15,291 --> 00:20:17,458
Hey! Were you driving Graham
without my permission?

437
00:20:17,541 --> 00:20:20,541
It wasn't me,
he drove over by himself!

438
00:20:20,625 --> 00:20:22,791
[GRAHAM]
Affirmative! It was me, Master.

439
00:20:22,875 --> 00:20:25,166
Alright, that's enough.
You're all too damn much.

440
00:20:25,250 --> 00:20:27,083
-[engine roaring]
-[VIDAUX] Let's go.

441
00:20:27,166 --> 00:20:30,291
♪

442
00:20:30,375 --> 00:20:31,541
[debris crumbling]

443
00:20:31,625 --> 00:20:33,166
[grunt]

444
00:20:57,416 --> 00:20:59,333
[GRAHAM]
No enemies detected behind us.

445
00:20:59,416 --> 00:21:01,791
She isn't following.

446
00:21:01,875 --> 00:21:03,583
Did you take any pictures?

447
00:21:03,666 --> 00:21:04,583
[chuckle]
Of course!

448
00:21:04,666 --> 00:21:06,250
Here!
[giggle]

449
00:21:07,208 --> 00:21:09,083
That's so cool!

450
00:21:09,166 --> 00:21:12,125
Oh yeah, Papa, did you find
the thingy you had to get?

451
00:21:13,250 --> 00:21:15,125
[VIDAUX]
Yeah...

452
00:21:17,208 --> 00:21:19,000
Hey, look, that's you!

453
00:21:19,083 --> 00:21:20,791
[YURI]
Wow, snazzy!

454
00:21:20,875 --> 00:21:22,375
Who's the other guy?

455
00:21:22,458 --> 00:21:24,041
[VIDAUX]
My old subordinate.

456
00:21:24,125 --> 00:21:26,083
He died in that city.

457
00:21:26,166 --> 00:21:29,541
His father was a cop, too.
He asked me to retrieve this.

458
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:32,125
It's the only record left
from when he was alive.

459
00:21:32,208 --> 00:21:33,791
♪

460
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:35,875
A legacy, he picked
the same career path

461
00:21:35,958 --> 00:21:37,791
as his dad, how nice.

462
00:21:37,875 --> 00:21:39,375
Though he never quite reached

463
00:21:39,458 --> 00:21:41,500
the same heights
that his father did.

464
00:21:43,750 --> 00:21:45,875
Anyway, how did you guys fare?

465
00:21:45,958 --> 00:21:48,000
[YURI] Oh, right!
We have to look at the video!

466
00:21:49,750 --> 00:21:51,666
Yvain.

467
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:53,541
Jaques.

468
00:21:53,625 --> 00:21:55,000
Derrida.

469
00:21:59,666 --> 00:22:00,833
Look, there!

470
00:22:01,791 --> 00:22:04,250
[YURI]
That's her, but who's she with?

471
00:22:05,208 --> 00:22:06,541
[DERRIDA]
That's...

472
00:22:09,291 --> 00:22:11,916
Cassiel.

